bug.short_desc: There is no appearance fallback for child controls

long_desc.thetext:
We ran into a problem with progress bars being child controls. At first sight, they seem to be broken when a explicit styling in Appearances.js is missing.
It would be nice to have a fallback or at least some error message telling the developer, that an appearance for the progress bars is missing.
Minimal code-example is attached.

Added additional message to inform the developer that a specific appearance ID cannot be resolved by the manager. This should help the developer to identify the widget / appearance which causes this issue.
Fixed with 78fe25a41c3f824fbd2e139e5da45dec0bfd3510 (master)

Added additional check for a undefined variable.
